abstract: AT&T, the network it seems everyone loves to hate, has unseated Sprint as the fastest 3G data service in a test by the technology Web site Gizmodo, which also tested Verizon and T-Mobile.

abstract: Five companies we heard a lot about in 2009, and some predictions of what we might expect from them over the next 365 days.
snippet: Five companies we heard a lot about in 2009, and some predictions of what we might expect from them over the next 365 days.
lead_paragraph: Unlike Conan O’Brien, I can’t predict what will happen in the year 3000, but 2010 looks as if it’s going to be an exciting year for technology companies. Here are five companies we heard a lot about in 2009, and some predictions of what we might expect from them over the next 365 days.
